benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/invoiceItems/{invoiceItemId}/customFields - Remove custom fields from invoice item

covered: Valid Deletion Scenarios (TC01-TC04) demonstrate 204 responses with removal of custom fields across various initial states (multiple fields, single field, no fields, and already empty).
Subset and large-scale field removal (TC02, TC12, TC18) verify removal of a subset of fields, a large number of fields, and duplicates are processed without errors.
Header/Authorization handling (TC06, TC09, TC19, TC20) cover presence of required header, missing header, invalid/expired token, and header parsing regression.

Error handling and input validation (TC07, TC08, TC10, TC15, TC17) cover invalid invoiceItemId format, non-existent items, malformed customField IDs, injection attempts, and partial valid/invalid IDs.
Parameter handling and resilience (TC11, TC13) cover extra/unexpected parameters and system under heavy load; long header (TC16) and dependency unavailability (TC14) demonstrate resilience scenarios.
gaps: Concurrency/race-condition testing is missing (two clients deleting simultaneously).
Soft-delete semantics testing is missing (if applicable).
403 Forbidden authorization path not explicitly tested (only 400 and 401 covered).
Caching behavior (ETag/Cache-Control) for DELETE not tested (if caching is relevant).
recommendations: Add explicit concurrency tests to verify idempotency and race conditions during deletion.
Add tests for soft-delete semantics or confirm they do not apply for this endpoint.
Add a dedicated 403 Forbidden test case to cover insufficient permissions scenarios.
Add tests for caching behavior on DELETE responses (ETag/Cache-Control) if caching is applicable.
Add rate-limiting tests to ensure proper behavior under bursts of DELETE requests.
Enhance error message validation for 4xx/5xx responses to ensure consistent payloads.
Expand header edge-case coverage to include more variations in casing and whitespace beyond TC20.
